# Git does not enforce file size limits; hosts (e.g. GitHub) reject blobs ~>100 MB.
# Use Git LFS for large tracked binaries: install once per clone with `git lfs install`.
#
# After installing Git LFS, uncomment the following so .bank files (and similar) are
# stored as LFS pointers instead of huge Git blobs. Push will still fail if a file
# was committed before LFS — use `git lfs migrate import` or history rewrite in that case.
#
# *.bank filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.strings.bank filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Line endings: prefer Unity/FMOD binary assets stay binary (no CRLF “corruption”)
*.bank binary
*.strings.bank binary
